<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_færsk" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>færsk</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>færskʼæ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>ребро</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>rib</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_færsk." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>max færsḱytæ nadæj nīk˳y væjjync cʼæl</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>наши ребра не бывают никогда поломаны от колотушек</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>our ribs are never broken by mallets</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>94</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>mæ zærond færskʼitæ min maci basæddæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>не поломай мои старые ребра</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>don't break my old ribs</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>24%l7–8%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>wærdony færsḱytæ</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>wærduni færskʼitæ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>ребра (вертикальные планки) арбы</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>ribs (vertical planks) of a bullock-cart</q></cit></sense><bibl><ref target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>III 13</biblScope></bibl></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>max færsḱytæ nadæj nīk˳y væjjync cʼæl</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>наши ребра не бывают никогда поломаны от колотушек</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>our ribs are never broken by mallets</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>94</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>mæ zærond færskʼitæ min maci basæddæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>не поломай мои старые ребра</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>don't break my old ribs</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>24%l7–8%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Производное от <xr><ref target="#entry_fars"/></xr> ‘бок’ (%i*pars(v)-ka%i). По типу образование ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_fæd"/></xr> и <xr><ref target="#entry_fædg"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_xus"/></xr> и <xr><ref target="#entry_x0yskʼ"/></xr>. Из многочисленных иранских соответствий приведем здесь только те, в которых, как в осетинском, выступает формант %ik%i(%ig%i): <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>pürsk</w><gloss><q>ребро</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Shaw"/><biblScope>245</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>pursiga</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/><w>pərsəγё</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*parsāk (prsʼk)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>pālsuā</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>. Остальные параллели см. под <xr><ref target="#entry_fars"/></xr> ‘бок’. %bГруз.%b <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>percx-ali</w><gloss><q>ребро</q></gloss></mentioned> представляет, возможно, старое заимствование из аланского.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>352</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">A derivative of <xr><ref target="#entry_fars"/></xr> ‘side’ (%i*pars(v)-ka%i). Cf. the similar derivation pattern in <xr><ref target="#entry_fæd"/></xr> and <xr><ref target="#entry_fædg"/></xr>, in <xr><ref target="#entry_xus"/></xr> and <xr><ref target="#entry_x0yskʼ"/></xr>. Of the numerous Iranian correspondences, we will cite here only those in which, as in the Ossetic, the formant %ik%i(%ig%i) appears: <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>pürsk</w><gloss><q>rib</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Shaw"/><biblScope>245</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>pursiga</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/><w>pərsəγё</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*parsāk (prsʼk)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>pālsuā</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>. Other parallels see under <xr><ref target="#entry_fars"/></xr> ‘side’. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>percx-ali</w><gloss><q>rib</q></gloss></mentioned> is probably an old borrowing from Alan.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>352</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>